description.narrative: This award strives to generate rapid, sustained, and broad-based economic growth. More specifically, this includes a Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Zambia: Funds used to further enable Peace Corps staff and Volunteers to train and support improvements of food production, and development of food security-related agricultural businesses.. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Headquarters Staff and Training: Funds used to provide HQ staff and training to allow Peace Corps to expand ongoing efforts in Africa to accelerate the food security response.. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Zambia: Funds used to further enable Peace Corps staff and Volunteers to train and support community partners and service providers in the improvements of food production, cultural and management methods, utilization. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - West Africa Regional Food Security Partnership: Funds used to provide funding to specific posts in West Africa to build community capacity at the grass-roots level to strategically respond to food security vulnerabil. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Senegal: Funds used to continue to further develop the master farmers program as well as develop food security hubs across Senegal.. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - West Africa Regional Food Security Partnership: Funds used to provide funding to specific posts in West Africa to build community capacity at the grass-roots level.. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Senegal: Funds used to continue to further develop the master farmers program as well as develop food security hubs across Senegal where Peace Corps Volunteers, counterparts and partners will strengthen market linkag. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Tanzania: Funds used to prepare Peace Corps Volunteers to make contributions Feed the Future goals, meet host country development needs and provide resources to properly support, monitor, and evaluate its contributi. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Uganda: Funds used to support Peace Corps Volunteers attend to food security needs that cross sector boundaries, often helping individual families and entire communities to increase their resiliency to food insecurit. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Uganda: Funds used to support Peace Corps Volunteers attend to food security needs that cross sector boundaries, often helping to increase their resiliency to food insecurity.. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Guatemala: Funds used to address food security needs by providing technical training for Peace Corps volunteers, staff and host-country counterparts to provide ongoing support in the implementation and monitoring and. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Ethiopia: Funds used to support Peace Corps Volunteers working with community leaders to mobilize their communities, helping those communities develop a local response to global food insecurity.. Global Food Security (GFS) Agreement - Africa Food Security: Funds used to provide funding for a food security advisor and program support to allow Peace Corps to better systematize and expand ongoing efforts in Africa to accelerate the food security resp.
To generate rapid, sustained, and broad-based economic growth.
